parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering light illuminates on the dashboard
the steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the vehicle jerks or slows down unexpectedly
the radio and other electrical components malfunction
and the vehicle may stall or become difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock up or become difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel locks up or becomes hard to turn
the vehicle pulls to one side
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
and the vehicle may stall or become difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the power steering system to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radio and other electrical components malfunction
the power steering light illuminates on the dashboard
and the vehicle may stall or become difficult to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: The airbag warning light on the dashboard comes on and stays on
the airbag warning light flickers or comes on intermittently
the airbag system fails to deploy in an accident
the airbag system deploys unnecessarily while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to jerk, stutter, or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts harshly
the vehicle jerks or stutters
the transmission slips into neutral
the vehicle loses power
the "check engine" and "automatic transmission" indicators illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic control module can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle's engine stalls
the transmission shifts erratically
the "check engine" and "automatic transmission" indicators illuminate
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.
